  "title": "IR spectrum of carbon dioxide",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents an infrared spectrum. The horizontal axis is labeled “Wavelength, in micrometers,” and the numbers 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 12, 14, and 16 are indicated at increasingly smaller intervals. The vertical axis is labeled “Intensity of Transmitted Radiation,” and the numbers 0 through 100, in increments of 20, are indicated. There are two sharp absorption bands on the spectrum. The graph begins approximately at 90 on the vertical axis, and moves steadily to the right before decreasing to slightly past 0 on the vertical axis at approximately 4.4 micrometers on the horizontal axis. The graph then increases back to approximately 90 before decreasing again to slightly past 0 on the vertical axis at approximately 14 micrometers on the horizontal axis. The graph then increases and ends at approximately 40 at 16 micrometers on the horizontal axis.\" height=\"284\" src=\"/images/74fe6dd3dbf05941a1546bb5b1b8146a.png\" width=\"500\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The infrared spectrum above represents the absorption of certain wavelengths of radiation by molecules of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C O 2\"><math alttext=\"C O 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following best explains what occurs at the molecular level as the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C O 2\"><math alttext=\"C O 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> molecules absorb photons of the infrared radiation?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The atoms in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C O 2\"><math alttext=\"C O 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> molecules increase their vibration as the bonds between the atoms bend and stretch.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The molecules of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C O 2\"><math alttext=\"C O 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>  increase the energy of their rotational motions.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The electrons in the valence shells of the atoms in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C O 2\"><math alttext=\"C O 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>  molecules are promoted to higher electronic energy levels.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The bonds between the atoms in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C O 2\"><math alttext=\"C O 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>  molecules are continuously broken and then re-form.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
